   investigated following the Dillon Creek Fire 1994. The fire occurred in
   Douglas-fir/hardwood forests located in the Klamath National Forest,
   northeastern California. A GIS was used to compile information from
   Landsat imagery, post-fire aerial photography, and ground observations.
